<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The dark glands on the sepals and the high altitude habitat confirm the affinity with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dumetorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea dumetorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is easily distinguished by its much larger corolla.
</paragraph>
